      "width": 560,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Field-Driven Edge Class Smoke\n\nThis graph is itself a candidate edge-class artifact under the new regime.\n\nWhat it should prove:\n- graph identity and doctrine live on the declaration\n- machine-readable contract data lives in field nodes\n- render defaults can be read from fields\n- a sample edge instance can mirror those defaults without relying on a manifest or legend"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "field-edge-class-smoke-spec",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Expected Readout",
      "position": {
        "x": 1080,
        "y": -260
      },
      "width": 600,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Expected Readout\n\nReader expectations:\n- `key` => `smoke.edge.link`\n- `label` => `Smoke Edge Link`\n- `meaning` => meaningful sample relationship\n- `renderDefaults.stroke` => `#2563eb`\n- `renderDefaults.width` => `4`\n- `renderDefaults.dash` => `solid`\n- `defaultEdgeType` => `reference`\n\nNo manifest or legend node should be required to derive the edge-class payload."
      }
    },
